work coverage is generally good in Ranchi, but may be limited in Netarhat and some remote areas. Jio and Airtel are reliable options.\n*   **Currency:** ATMs are available in Ranchi. Carry sufficient cash for Netarhat as ATM availability might be limited. Exchange currency in Ranchi at reputable exchange agencies.\n*   **Medical Facilities:** Raj Hospital (Ranchi) is a good option for medical emergencies. Check Google Maps for clinics in Ranchi.\n\n**Important Contact Information:**\n*   Railway Enquiry: 139\n*   Tourist Information (Jharkhand Tourism): +91-651-2490421\n*   Emergency Services: 112 (Police, Fire, Ambulance)\n\n**Total Estimated Cost: ₹24320 for 2 people + Hotel**\n**Total estimated cost for hotels: 3 Nights: (₹30000-₹40000).**\n**GRAND TOTAL: ₹54,320 - ₹64,320 for 2 People.**\n\nThis itinerary provides a packed yet enjoyable experience, balancing sightseeing, cultural immersion, and relaxation within your budget. Remember to confirm costs and availability of accommodations and activities in advance. Enjoy your trip to Jharkhand!\n','{\"days\": 3, \"budget\": 100000, \"interests\": [\"Shopping\", \"Food & Cuisine\", \"Nightlife\", \"Adventure Activities\", \"Beaches\"], \"group_size\": 2, \"destinations\": [\"Ranchi\", \"Netarhat\", \"Hundru Falls\"], \"travel_style\": \"packed\"}','2025-09-17 22:34:51',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,'2025-09-18 04:04:51','2025-09-18 04:04:51'),('itinerary_20250918_090209','9ffdf221-c444-4eb2-b15b-8f9693adc0b0','Netarhat',5,25000.00,'**TRIP PARAMETERS:**\n- Destinations: Netarhat\n- Duration: 5 days\n- Budget: ₹25000 for 2 people\n- Interests: Nightlife (limited in Netarhat, focusing on stargazing and bonfire), Mountains, Historical Places\n- Travel Style: packed\n- Group Size: 2 people\n\n**Day 1: Arrival & Sunset Spectacle**\n• Morning (8:00 AM): Arrive at Ranchi Airport/Railway Station. Hire a pre-booked taxi to Netarhat. Travel time approximately 4-5 hours (₹2500-₹3000 for the taxi).\n• Mid-morning (10:30 AM): Stop for breakfast en route at a local dhaba near Chandwa. Enjoy authentic Litti Chokha and Chai (₹150 per person).\n• Afternoon (2:00 PM): Check into your pre-booked accommodation in Netarhat. Freshen up and relax after the journey.\n• Evening (4:00 PM): Visit Magnolia Point, a famous sunset viewpoint. Enjoy the breathtaking view of the valley. (Entry Free)\n• Evening (6:00 PM): Return to the hotel. In the evening, arrange for a bonfire at your accommodation (check with the hotel for charges, approx. ₹500-₹1000) and enjoy stargazing. This is as close to \'nightlife\' as you\'ll get in Netarhat.\n\n**Estimated Day 1 Cost (excluding hotel): ₹2000 per person**\n\n**Day 2: Exploring Nature\'s Bounty**\n• Morning (8:00 AM): Visit Netarhat School, a historical boarding school known for its colonial architecture and scenic campus. (Entry Free, but respect school timings if it\'s a weekday)\n• Mid-morning (10:30 AM): Trek to Koel View Point. Hire a local guide (₹300-₹500) for a safer and more informative experience. Pack water and snacks.\n• Afternoon (2:00 PM): Have lunch at a local restaurant, try a Thali meal with local vegetables (₹200 per person).\n• Evening (4:00 PM): Visit Lower Ghaghri Falls. Enjoy the cascading waterfall and the surrounding natural beauty. (Entry Fee: ₹20 per person).\n• Evening (6:00 PM): Explore the local market. Buy local handicrafts or souvenirs (budget ₹500). Dinner at a local restaurant (₹250 per person).\n\n**Estimated Day 2 Cost (excluding hotel): ₹1020 per person**\n\n**Day 3: Tribal Culture & Waterfalls**\n• Morning (8:00 AM): Visit the Betla National Park (requires permits, book in advance online or through your hotel). This involves a longer journey (1-2 hours each way). Hire a Jeep Safari (₹2500-₹3000 per Jeep, split between two people).\n• Mid-morning (10:30 AM): Explore Betla National Park. Try spotting wildlife like deer, elephants, and various bird species.\n• Afternoon (2:00 PM): Return to Netarhat for lunch. Try a tribal specialty dish if availa