icated to Lord Shiva. Climb the steps for stunning city views. Cost: Free, but budget ₹50 for offerings/prasad.\n• Afternoon (2:00 PM): Explore the Albert Ekka Chowk, a central landmark and learn about the war hero Albert Ekka. Travel time: 10 minutes. Cost: Free.\n• Evening (6:00 PM): Enjoy a traditional tribal dance performance at a local cultural center (if available – inquire at the hotel about timings and availability). Cost: ₹300 per person. Alternatively, enjoy dinner at a restaurant serving tribal cuisine. Cost: ₹400 per person.\n\n**Estimated Day 2 Cost (excluding hotel): ₹800 per person**\n\n**Day 3: Waterfall Wonders**\n• Morning (8:00 AM): Visit Hundru Falls. Witness the cascading waters of the Subarnarekha River. Travel time: 1.5 hours. Cost: ₹500 per person (shared taxi). ₹50 entry fee.\n• Mid-morning (11:00 AM): Enjoy the scenic beauty and take photographs.  \n• Afternoon (2:00 PM): Visit Jonha Falls (Gautamdhara Falls). Another beautiful waterfall with a serene atmosphere. Travel time: 45 minutes. Cost: ₹300 per person (shared taxi). ₹30 entry fee.\n• Evening (6:00 PM): Return to Ranchi. Relax or explore local markets for souvenirs. Cost: ₹200 per person (souvenirs).\n\n**Estimated Day 3 Cost (excluding hotel): ₹1080 per person**\n\n**Day 4: Nature\'s Embrace at Dassam Falls**\n• Morning (8:00 AM): Travel to Dassam Falls, another spectacular waterfall on the Kanchi River. Travel time: 2 hours. Cost: ₹600 per person (shared taxi). ₹30 entry fee.\n• Mid-morning (10:30 AM): Explore the falls and enjoy the natural beauty.\n• Afternoon (2:00 PM): Picnic lunch near the falls (pack your own).\n• Evening (6:00 PM): Return to Ranchi. Cost: ₹600 per person (shared taxi).\n\n**Estimated Day 4 Cost (excluding hotel): ₹1230 per person**\n\n**Day 5: Zoological Park and Lakeside Serenity**\n• Morning (9:00 AM): Visit Birsa Zoological Park (Ormanjhi). Observe diverse wildlife in a natural habitat. Travel time: 45 minutes. Cost: ₹200 per person (taxi). ₹80 entry fee.