Always ask for permission before taking photographs of people or their homes.\n• Dress code recommendations: Dress modestly, covering shoulders and knees.\n• Interaction guidelines: Be respectful of their customs and traditions. Listen attentively and avoid interrupting.\n\n**Sustainable Tourism Practices:**\n• Local economy support: Purchase souvenirs from local artisans and businesses.\n• Environmental conservation: Avoid littering and damaging the environment.\n• Community respect: Be mindful of the local culture and customs.\n\n**Practical Tips:**\n• **Best Time to Visit:** October to March (pleasant weather).\n• **Mobile Connectivity:** Good network coverage in Ranchi city. Coverage may be spotty in remote areas. Jio and Airtel are reliable providers.\n• **Currency:** ATMs are widely available in Ranchi. Exchange facilities are available at the airport and major banks.\n• **Medical Facilities:** Raj Hospital (0651-2547011), Medica Hospital (0651-7100100)\n\n**Important Contact Information:**\n• Railway Enquiry: 139\n• Tourist Information: Jharkhand Tourism Development Corporation (JTDC) - 0651-2560521\n• Emergency Services: 112 (Police/Fire/Ambulance)\n\n**Total Estimated Cost (excluding accommodation and shopping): ₹63770 for 5 people**\n\n**Note:** Accommodation costs will vary depending on your choice of hotel and are *not* included in the total cost. Assuming 13 nights at ₹4000 per night (2 rooms), the total accommodation cost will be approximately ₹52000. This puts the total estimated trip cost *excluding shopping* at approximately ₹115770, exceeding your original budget. You may need to adjust some activities or choose a more budget-friendly accommodation option to stay within the ₹100000 limit. Prioritize waterfall visits and the tribal village experience as core activities, and look for cheaper alternatives to nightlife or eating at upscale restaurants if needed. Consider guesthouses or homestays for accommodation to significantly cut costs.\n','{\"days\": 14, \"budget\": 100000, \"interests\": [\"culturalSites\", \"Nature & Wildlife\", \"Nightlife\"], \"group_size\": 5, \"destinations\": [\"Ranchi\"], \"travel_style\": \"balanced\"}','2025-09-18 07:57:06',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,'2025-09-18 13:27:05','2025-09-18 13:27:05'),('itinerary_20250919_002530','9ffdf221-c444-4eb2-b15b-8f9693adc0b0','Betla National Park',5,50000.00,'**TRIP PARAMETERS:**\n- Destinations: Betla National Park\n- Duration: 5 days\n- Budget: ₹50000 for 3 people\n- Interests: Mountains\n- Travel Style: balanced\n- Group Size: 3 people\n\n**Day 1: Arrival and Park Exploration**\n• Morning (8:00 AM): Arrival at Daltonganj Railway Station (DTO). Hire a pre-booked taxi to Betla (approx. 1.5 hours, 25 km). Cost: ₹1200 for the taxi. Check in to your accommodation.\n• Mid-morning (10:30 AM): Obtain entry permits and hire a guide for Betla National Park safari. Entry fee: ₹250 per person. Guide fee: ₹800 (fixed).\n• Afternoon (2:00 PM): Afternoon jeep safari in Betla National Park. Explore the core area; spot deer, elephants (if lucky!), and various bird species. Safari Duration: 3 hours. Jeep Safari Cost: ₹2800 (shared by 3). Travel time within the park accounted for.\n• Evening (6:00 PM): Enjoy a traditional dinner at your accommodation or a local dhaba. Try *Dhuska* (rice flour and dal fritters) with *Aloo Chokha* (mashed potato). Cost: ₹300 per person. This is a popular evening snack in the region.\n\n**Estimated Day 1 Cost (excluding hotel): ₹1983 per person**\n\n**Day 2: Forts and Waterfalls**\n• Morning (8:00 AM): After breakfast, visit Palamu Forts (Old and New), located within Betla National Park (approx. 1 hour drive from main Betla area). Explore the historical ruins and enjoy panoramic views.\n• Mid-morning (10:30 AM): Explore the Old Fort first. Entry to the Forts is included in the National Park entry ticket from yesterday. Hire a local guide at the fort for insights into its history. Guide cost ₹500 (shared).\n• Afternoon (2:00 PM): Drive to Mirchaiya Falls (approximately 1.5 hours from Palamu Forts). Enjoy the natural beauty and spend some time relaxing. Pack lunch to enjoy by the falls. Packaged lunch: ₹200 per person.\n• Evening (6:00 PM): Return to Betla. Enjoy a bonfire at your accommodation (if available) and share stories. Cost for bonfire materials and setup (shared): ₹300. Experience the quiet of the night and listen to local folklore from your guide or accommodation staff.\n\n**Estimated Day 2 Cost (excluding hotel): ₹533 per person**\n\n**Day 3: Tribal Culture and Local Markets**\n• Morning (8:00 AM): Visit a nearby tribal village (Orion Village, speak to your accommodation to arrange). Interact with the local Oraon community, learning about their customs, traditions, and way of life. Arrange this through your hotel, who will facilitate proper permissions and ensure respectful interaction. Cost (donation to the village for allowing the visit, coordinated by your hotel): ₹500 total (shared).\n• Mid-morning (10:30 AM): Participate in a traditional Oraon dance (arranged through the village elder – your hotel will handle this). Cost (honorarium for dancers, arranged via hotel): ₹1000 (shared).\n• Afternoon (2:00 PM): Visit Daltonganj Market (approx. 1.5-hour drive). Explore the local handicrafts, textiles, and produce. It\'s a vibrant market showcasing local culture. Travel cost via pre-booked taxi (round trip): ₹1200 (shared).\n• Evening (6:00 PM): Enjoy dinner at a local restaurant in Daltonganj. Try *Litti Chokha* (wheat balls stuffed with sattu and roasted, served with mashed vegetables) – a popular Bihari/Jharkhandi dish. Cost: ₹350 per person.\n\n**Estimated Day 3 Cost (excluding hotel): ₹1083 per person**\n\n**Day 4: Second Safari and Sunset Views**\n• Morning (6:00 AM): Early morning jeep safari in Betla National Park. Focus on different areas of the park than your first safari, increasing your chances of spotting different wildlife. Cost: ₹2800 (shared).\n• Mid-morning (9:00 AM): Breakfast at your accommodation after the safari. Included in hotel stay.\n• Afternoon (2:00 PM): Visit Kechki Sangam (approx. 1-hour drive), the confluence of the North Koel and Burha rivers. The scenic beauty is captivating. Travel cost via pre-booked taxi (round trip): ₹1000 (shared).\n• Evening (4:00 PM): Find a good spot near Kechki Sangam for enjoying the sunset over the river. Pack snacks and water. Snacks: ₹150 per person.\n• Evening (6:00 PM): Return to Betla and relax.\n\n**Estimated Day 4 Cost (excluding hotel): ₹1183 per person**\n\n**Day 5: Departure**\n• Morning (8:00 AM): Enjoy a leisurely breakfast.\n• Mid-morning (10:00 AM): Visit the Betla National Park Museum (if you haven\'t already). Entry: ₹50 per person.\n• Afternoon (12:00 PM): Check out from your accommodation.\n• Afternoon (1:00 PM): Have lunch at a local dhaba near Betla. Cost: ₹300 per person.\n• Afternoon (2:30 PM): Transfer to Daltonganj Railway Station for your departure (pre-booked taxi: ₹1200).\n\n**Estimated Day 5 Cost (excluding hotel): ₹750 per person**\n\n**Important Notes Before You Start:**\n• **Respect:** Be mindful of local customs and traditions. Dress modestly, especially when visiting tribal villages. Always ask for permission before taking photos of people.\n• **Bargaining:** Bargaining is common in local markets. Start with a lower price and negotiate politely.\n• **Environmental Responsibility:** Avoid littering and dispose of waste responsibly. Support eco-friendly initiatives and businesses.\n• **Flexibility:** Weather conditions can change rapidly, especially during monsoon. Be prepared to adjust your itinerary accordingly. Safari timings can change; confirm in advance.\n• **Safety:** Keep your valuables safe. Be aware of your surroundings and avoid walking alone at night. Emergency contacts are listed below.\n• **Language:** Learning a few basic Hindi phrases can be helpful. *Namaste* (hello), *Dhanyavad* (thank you), *Kitna hai?* (How much?).\n\n**Accommodation Recommendation:**\n*Van Vihar Eco Resort, Betla:* A comfortable and eco-friendly option with well-appointed rooms and delicious food. They can help organize safaris and village visits. Phone: +91 94311 70007. Website: (Check online directories and travel booking sites). This recommendation offers a balanced experience of comfort and proximity to the park.\n\n**Cultural Etiquette Tips for Tribal Areas:**\n• **Photography permissions:** Always ask for permission before taking photos, especially of individuals. Offer a small donation in return for their cooperation.\n• **Dress code recommendations:** Dress modestly. Avoid revealing clothing.\n• **Interaction guidelines:** Be respectful and polite. Avoid making loud noises or disturbing their peace. Communicate through a translator if needed. Accept offerings of food and drink if offered.\n\n**Sustainable Tourism Practices:**\n• **Local economy support:** Purchase handicrafts and souvenirs from local artisans and businesses.\n• **Environmental conservation:** Avoid using single-use plastics. Carry your own reusable water bottle and shopping bag.\n• **Community respect:** Learn about the local culture and traditions. Participate in responsible tourism activities that benefit the community.\n\n**Practical Tips:**\n• **Best Time to Visit:** October to March (winter season) is the most pleasant time to visit Betla. The weather is cool and dry, making it ideal for wildlife viewing.\n• **Mobile Connectivity:** BSNL and Airtel provide decent mobile network coverage in Betla and Daltonganj. However, connectivity can be patchy in remote areas.\n• **Currency:** ATMs are available in Daltonganj. It\'s advisable to carry sufficient cash as credit card acceptance may be limited in smaller establishments.\n• **Medical Facilities:** Primary healthcare facilities are available in Betla. A larger hospital is located in Daltonganj: Medanta Multi Speciality Hospital, Daltonganj (Contact details available online).\n\n**Important Contact Information:**\n• Railway Enquiry: 139\n• Tourist Information (Jharkhand Tourism): +91 651-2491517 (General Inquiry – specific Daltonganj office information may be difficult to find online; best to inquire upon arrival).\n• Emergency Services: 112 (India Emergency Number)\n\n**Total Estimated Cost: ₹11,500 per person = ₹34,500 for 3 people (excluding hotel).** The hotel costs will depend on your choice but a budget of ₹15,500 for 5 nights for 3 people is reasonable for a mid-range hotel like Van Vihar Eco Resort.\n**Grand Total Estimated Cost: ₹50,000 for 3 people.**\n','{\"days\": 5, \"budget\": 50000, \"interests\": [\"Mountains\"], \"group_size\": 3, \"destinations\": [\"Betla National Park\"], \"travel_style\": \"balanced\"}','2025-09-18 18:55:30',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,'2025-09-19 00:25:30','2025-09-19 00:25:30'),('itinerary_20250919_002737','9ffdf221-c444-4eb2-b15b-8f9693adc0b0','Netarhat, Betla National Park, Hazaribagh',5,25000.00,'Okay, here\'s a detailed 5-day travel itinerary for Netarhat, Betla National Park, and Hazaribagh, Jharkhand, designed to fit your specified parameters and format.\n\n**TRIP PARAMETERS:**\n*   Destinations: Netarhat, Betla National Park, Hazaribagh\n*   Duration: 5 days\n*   Budget: ₹25000 for 2 people\n*   Interests: Shopping, Nature & Wildlife, Nightlife\n*   Travel Style: balanced\n*   Group Size: 2 people\n\n**Day 1: Netarhat Sunrise & Scenic Beauty**\n*   Morning (8:00 AM): Reach Netarhat. Check in to your pre-booked accommodation (see accommodation recommendation below). Freshen up and have breakfast at your hotel or a local eatery (₹150 per person).\n*   Mid-morning (10:30 AM): Visit Netarhat School. Explore the historical school campus and learn about its legacy (Entry Free). Enjoy the serene atmosphere.\n*   Afternoon (2:00 PM): Travel to Magnolia Point (Sunset Point) (Approx. 30 mins travel). Have lunch at a local dhaba en route. Try the traditional \"Dhuska\" (rice flour preparation) (₹200 per person).\n*   Evening (6:00 PM): Witness the breathtaking sunset at Magnolia Point. This location is famous for its tragic love story and the panoramic views.  Savor local \"Chai\" from a vendor.  (₹30 per person). Afterwards, enjoy stargazing (weather permitting).\n\n**Estimated Day 1 Cost (excluding hotel): ₹380 per person**\n\n**Day 2: Waterfalls and Local Culture of Netarhat**\n*   Morning (8:00 AM): After breakfast, head to Lodh Falls, one of Jharkhand\'s highest waterfalls (approx. 2-hour drive from Netarhat). Hire a local jeep for the round trip (₹1500 - split between 2 = ₹750 per person).\n*   Mid-morning (10:30 AM): Explore Lodh Falls. Enjoy the cascading water and the surrounding natural beauty.  Hire a local guide (optional, ₹200, split = ₹100 per person) to learn about the local flora and fauna.\n*   Afternoon (2:00 PM): Have lunch at a local restaurant or pack a picnic lunch to enjoy near the falls (₹250 per person). Try \"Litti Chokha\", a popular Jharkhandi dish.\n*   Evening (6:00 PM): Visit the local Netarhat market. Experience the local culture, interact with villagers, and maybe buy some tribal handicrafts or local produce as souvenirs.  (Shopping budget - variable, but budget ₹500 total = ₹250 per person). Evening is free to take a walk in nature in the vicinities.\n\n**Estimated Day 2 Cost (excluding hotel): ₹1350 per person**\n\n**Day 3: Wildlife Safari at Betla National Park**\n*   Morning (6:00 AM): Early start! Check out from your Netarhat hotel. Travel from Netarhat to Betla National Park (approx. 3-hour drive). Hire a private car for the journey (₹2500, split = ₹1250 per person).\n*   Mid-morning (9:00 AM): Check into your accommodation near Betla National Park. Freshen up and have breakfast.\n*   Afternoon (2:00 PM): Embark on an afternoon jeep safari in Betla National Park.  Safari costs approximately ₹2000 per jeep (shared between 2 = ₹1000 per person) plus entry fees (₹200 per person).\n*   Evening (6:00 PM): Enjoy dinner at your hotel or a local restaurant. Nighttime jungle walk with a local guide for bird watching (₹500 split = ₹250 per person - *optional*).\n\n**Estimated Day 3 Cost (excluding hotel): ₹2700 per person**\n\n**Day 4: Betla to Hazaribagh - Lakes and Relaxation**\n*   Morning (8:00 AM): After breakfast, take a final short nature walk around Betla.\n*   Mid-morning (11:00 AM): Check out from your Betla accommodation. Travel from Betla to Hazaribagh (approx. 4-hour drive). Hire a car (₹3000, split = ₹1500 per person).\n*   Afternoon (3:00 PM): Check into your hotel in Hazaribagh. Have lunch (₹300 per person).\n*   Evening (6:00 PM): Visit Hazaribagh Lake. Enjoy the sunset and a peaceful boat ride (₹100 per person). Explore the local market near the lake (Shopping - variable, budget ₹500 total = ₹250 per person). Experience local street food like \"Samosas\" and \"Jalebis\" (₹100 per person).\n\n**Estimated Day 4 Cost (excluding hotel): ₹2250 per person**\n\n**Day 5: Hazaribagh Exploration & Departure**\n*   Morning (8:00 AM): Visit Hazaribagh National Park. Enjoy a morning walk/drive through the park. Entry fee ₹50 per person, vehicle entry fee ₹200 (split = ₹100 per person).\n*   Mid-morning (10:30 AM): Explore Canary Hill. Enjoy panoramic views of Hazaribagh town (Entry fee ₹20 per person).\n*   Afternoon (1:00 PM): Have a final lunch in Hazaribagh, trying a local Thali (₹300 per person).\n*   Evening (4:00 PM): Depart from Hazaribagh. You can take a train or bus to your next destination. Travel costs not included in the daily estimate.\n\n**Estimated Day 5 Cost (excluding travel): ₹470 per person**\n\n**Important Notes Before You Start:**\n\n*   **Respect:** Be respectful of local customs and traditions, especially in tribal areas. Ask for permission before taking photographs of people.\n*   **Bargaining:** Bargain respectfully in local markets. A good starting point is usually 50-70% of the quoted price.\n*   **Environmental Responsibility:** Avoid littering. Use reusable water bottles and minimize your environmental impact.\n*   **Flexibility:** Weather in Jharkhand can be unpredictable. Be prepared to adjust your itinerary if needed.\n*   **Safety:** Carry a basic first-aid kit. Be aware of your surroundings, especially at night.\n*   **Language:** Learning a few basic Hindi or local phrases will enhance your experience. (Namaste - Hello, Dhanyavad - Thank you, Kitna Hai? - How much?)\n\n**Accommodation Recommendation:**\n\n*   **Netarhat:** *Hotel Prabhat Vihar (Jharkhand Tourism Development Corporation)*. Contact: 06569-277224. Recommended for its location and basic amenities. Booking in advance is essential. Budget ₹2500-₹3500 per night.\n*   **Betla:** *Van Vihar, Betla*. Contact: 09934510676. Cottages near Betla National Park. Budget ₹2000 - ₹3000 per night.\n*   **Hazaribagh:** *Hotel Skylark*. Contact: 06546-263285. A comfortable hotel with good amenities. Budget ₹2000-₹3000 per night.\n\n**Cultural Etiquette Tips for Tribal Areas:**\n\n*   **Photography permissions:** Always ask permission before taking photographs of tribal people.\n*   **Dress code recommendations:** Dress modestly, especially when visiting villages.\n*   **Interaction guidelines:** Be polite and respectful. Avoid loud noises or disruptive behavior.\n\n**Sustainable Tourism Practices:**\n\n*   **Local economy support:** Buy souvenirs and handicrafts from local artisans.\n*   **Environmental conservation:** Support eco-friendly accommodations and activities.\n*   **Community respect:** Learn about and respect the local culture and traditions.\n\n**Practical Tips:**\n\n*   **Best Time to Visit:** October to March (winter season) is ideal for pleasant weather and wildlife sightings.\n*   **Mobile Connectivity:** BSNL and Airtel have relatively better network coverage in these areas, but expect limited connectivity in remote locations.\n*   **Currency:** ATMs are available in Hazaribagh and close to Betla, but it\'s advisable to carry sufficient cash, especially for Netarhat. SBI is the most common bank.\n*   **Medical Facilities:** Hazaribagh has a district hospital. In case of emergencies in Netarhat or Betla, you may need to travel to Daltonganj or Hazaribagh.\n    *   *Hazaribagh Sadar Hospital*: 06546-262222\n\n**Important Contact Information:**\n\n*   Railway Enquiry: 139\n*   Tourist Information (Jharkhand Tourism): 1800-123-6527 (Toll-Free)\n*   Emergency Services: 100 (Police), 101 (Fire), 102 (Ambulance)\n\n**Total Estimated Cost: ₹12,500 per person (excluding hotel and train travel)**\nHotel costs for 4 nights will be approx. ₹10,000 for 2 people. Total cost for the trip will then be ₹25,000.\n','{\"days\": 5, \"budget\": 25000, \"interests\": [\"Shopping\", \"Nature & Wildlife\", \"Nightlife\"], \"group_size\": 2, \"destinations\": [\"Netarhat\", \"Betla National Park\", \"Hazaribagh\"], \"travel_style\": \"balanced\"}','2025-09-18 18:57:38',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,'2025-09-19 00:27:37','2025-09-19 00:27:37'),('itinerary_20250919_020338','9ffdf221-c444-4eb2-b15b-8f9693adc0b0','Parasnath Hill, Betla National Park',3,25000.00,'**TRIP PARAMETERS:**\n- Destinations: Parasnath Hill, Betla National Park\n- Duration: 3 days\n- Budget: ₹25000 for 2 people\n- Interests: Religious Sites, Nature & Wildlife, culturalSites, Shopping\n- Travel Style: Packed\n- Group Size: 2 people\n\n**Day 1: Spiritual Ascent & Local Immersion**\n• Morning (8:00 AM): Arrival at Parasnath Railway Station (PNME). Take a pre-booked auto-rickshaw/taxi (₹200-₹300) to Madhuban (base of Parasnath Hill). Madhuban is a bustling town filled with religious significance for Jains.\n• Mid-morning (10:30 AM): Begin the trek to Shikharji (Parasnath Hill). This is the most sacred Jain pilgrimage site. Pack light! Hiring a Doli (palanquin) for the ascent is an option for those who prefer not to walk (₹3000-₹5000, negotiable depending on weight and stamina). The trek itself is free.\n• Afternoon (2:00 PM): Reach the summit. Visit the various Jain shrines (Tonks) dedicated to the 24 Tirthankaras. Spend time in quiet contemplation and take in the panoramic views. *Travel time:* The ascent takes approximately 4-5 hours, depending on your pace.\n• Evening (6:00 PM): Begin the descent. Aim to reach Madhuban by nightfall. Enjoy a traditional vegetarian Jain meal at a local restaurant. Try \'Dal Bafla\', a regional specialty (₹150-₹200 per person). Experience the evening Aarti at Bhomiyaji Temple in Madhuban, a significant Jain temple known for its spiritual atmosphere.\n\n**Estimated Day 1 Cost (excluding hotel): ₹2000 per person (including Doli cost; adjust if you trek independently)**\n\n**Day 2: Wildlife Adventure & Tribal Culture**\n• Morning (8:00 AM): After breakfast in Madhuban, hire a taxi (₹2500-₹3000) to Betla National Park (approx. 4-5 hours drive).\n• Mid-morning (12:30 PM): Check in at your pre-booked accommodation near Betla. (See accommodation recommendation below). Freshen up and have lunch. Try \'Dhuska\', a popular Jharkhandi snack made from rice and lentil flour (₹50-₹80 per plate).\n• Afternoon (2:00 PM): Begin a jeep safari in Betla National Park (₹1800-₹2500 per jeep, shared by 6 people, so ₹600-₹850 for the two of you). Opt for the afternoon safari as it increases your chances of spotting wildlife. Remember to carry your camera! The park entry fee is ₹50 per person.\n• Evening (6:00 PM): Engage with local tribal culture. Visit a nearby village (ask your jeep driver for recommendations; tip them extra - ₹200-₹300 - for the effort). Observe their lifestyle (respectfully and from a distance), traditional art, and perhaps even witness a local dance performance if available (arrange in advance through your hotel for an authentic experience; expect to pay ₹1000-₹2000 for a small performance for 2).\n\n**Estimated Day 2 Cost (excluding hotel): ₹2450 per person**\n\n**Day 3: Fort Exploration & Return Journey**\n• Morning (8:00 AM): After breakfast, visit Palamu Fort (Old and New Fort) within Betla National Park (₹20 entry fee per person). The forts are historically significant and offer insights into the region\'s past. Hire a local guide for a more in-depth understanding (₹500-₹800).\n• Mid-morning (10:30 AM): Explore the Betla Village market. Purchase local handicrafts, tribal jewelry, and souvenirs. Bargain respectfully! (Budget ₹500-₹1000 for shopping).\n• Afternoon (1:00 PM): Have lunch at a local restaurant in Betla. Sample \'Litti Chokha\', another Jharkhandi staple made of wheat balls stuffed with sattu (roasted gram flour) and served with mashed potatoes and eggplant (₹100-₹150 per person).\n• Evening (4:00 PM): Hire a taxi (₹2500-₹3000) from Betla to Daltonganj Railway Station (DTO) for your onward journey. Ensure your train departs late evening to allow for potential delays.\n\n**Estimated Day 3 Cost: ₹2100 per person**\n\n**Important Notes Before You Start:**\n• **Respect:** Be respectful of Jain religious practices at Parasnath Hill. Maintain silence within the temples and dress modestly. In tribal areas, always ask for permission before taking photographs.\n• **Bargaining:** Bargaining is common in local markets, especially for handicrafts and souvenirs. Start with a lower price than you\'re willing to pay and negotiate respectfully.\n• **Environmental Responsibility:** Avoid littering in the national park and on the trek to Parasnath Hill. Carry reusable water bottles.\n• **Flexibility:** Weather can be unpredictable. Be prepared for rain, especially during the monsoon season. Adjust your itinerary accordingly.\n• **Safety:** Carry a basic first-aid kit. Inform someone about your trekking plans. Beware of monkeys near temples; don\'t feed them. In the National Park, follow the guide\'s instructions.\n• **Language:** Basic Hindi will be helpful. Learn a few local phrases like \"Namaste\" (hello), \"Dhanyabad\" (thank you), and \"Kitna hai?\" (how much?).\n\n**Accommodation Recommendation:**\n* **Van Vihar, Betla National Park:** (Contact: +91-9431144923, Website: You will need to book through Jharkhand Tourism Development Corporation (JTDC) website or contact them directly). This is a reasonably priced option right inside the park, offering basic but comfortable accommodation. This maximizes your time in the park. Price: ₹2000-₹3000 per night for a double room.\n\n**Cultural Etiquette Tips for Tribal Areas:**\n• **Photography permissions:** Always ask for permission before taking photographs of tribal people. Offering a small amount of money (₹50-₹100) as a gesture of respect is common.\n• **Dress code recommendations:** Dress modestly, covering shoulders and knees. Avoid revealing clothing.\n• **Interaction guidelines:** Be polite and respectful. Avoid making loud noises or disruptive behavior. Do not offer alcohol or tobacco.\n\n**Sustainable Tourism Practices:**\n• **Local economy support:** Purchase local handicrafts and souvenirs from local artisans. Eat at local restaurants and support small businesses.\n• **Environmental conservation:** Avoid littering. Use reusable water bottles. Support eco-friendly tourism initiatives.\n• **Community respect:** Be respectful of local customs and traditions. Learn about the local culture and history.\n\n**Practical Tips:**\n• **Best Time to Visit:** October to March is the ideal time to visit, as the weather is pleasant. Avoid the monsoon season (June to September) due to heavy rainfall.\n• **Mobile Connectivity:** Mobile connectivity can be patchy in Betla National Park. BSNL generally has the best coverage.\n• **Currency:** ATMs are available in Daltonganj and Madhuban. It\'s advisable to carry enough cash, especially for expenses within the National Park.\n• **Medical Facilities:** Basic medical facilities are available in Daltonganj. In case of emergencies, consult your hotel for the nearest hospital.\n\n**Important Contact Information:**\n• Railway Enquiry: 139\n• Tourist Information: Jharkhand Tourism Development Corporation (JTDC): +91-9570247120 (Check the JTDC website for updated numbers.)\n• Emergency Services: 112 (National Emergency Number)\n\n**Total Estimated Cost: ₹23100 for 2 people (excluding train fares).** This leaves approximately ₹1900 for unexpected expenses and railway tickets.\n','{\"days\": 3, \"budget\": 25000, \"interests\": [\"Religious Sites\", \"Nature & Wildlife\", \"culturalSites\", \"Shopping\"], \"group_size\": 2, \"destinations\": [\"Parasnath Hill\", \"Betla National Park\"], \"travel_style\": \"packed\"}','2025-09-18 20:33:39',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,'2025-09-19 02:03:38','2025-09-19 02:03:38'),('itinerary_20250919_055415','9ffdf221-c444-4eb2-b15b-8f9693adc0b0','Netarhat',3,25000.00,'**TRIP PARAMETERS:**\n- Destinations: Netarhat\n- Duration: 3 days\n- Budget: ₹25000 for 2 people\n- Interests: Photography\n- Travel Style: balanced\n- Group Size: 2 people\n\n**Day 1: Sunrise & Serenity**\n• Morning (6:00 AM): Sunrise at Magnolia Point (Koel View Point). Arrive early to secure a good spot. This viewpoint offers panoramic views of the valleys, perfect for photography.\n• Mid-morning (8:30 AM): Breakfast at your hotel. (Included in accommodation). Alternatively, try local street food near the market for a taste of *dhuska* (savory fried rice cakes). (₹100 per person)\n• Afternoon (11:00 AM): Lower Ghaghri Falls. (Travel time: 1 hour). A scenic waterfall amidst dense forests. Capture the cascading water and surrounding landscapes. Entry Fee: ₹20 per person\n• Late Afternoon (2:00 PM): Upper Ghaghri Falls. (Travel time: 30 mins from Lower Ghaghri) Another beautiful waterfall, perfect for landscape photography. Wear comfortable shoes for the short trek.\n• Evening (6:00 PM): Sunset at Netarhat School. (Travel time: 15 mins). A historical boarding school with stunning views, especially beautiful during sunset. Photography of the school\'s architecture and the surrounding landscape is encouraged. Interact respectfully with any students or staff you encounter.\n\n**Estimated Day 1 Cost (excluding hotel): ₹250 per person**\n\n**Day 2: Exploring Tribal Culture and Nature\'s Embrace**\n• Morning (9:00 AM): Visit the Netarhat Government Museum (₹30 per person). Learn about the local tribal culture, history, and art. Photography is usually allowed, but confirm beforehand.\n• Mid-morning (11:00 AM): Explore the local market (Netarhat Bazaar). Experience the vibrant atmosphere, photograph local produce, handicrafts, and interact with vendors. Purchase local honey or bamboo crafts as souvenirs. (₹500 for souvenirs and snacks for two) Bargain respectfully.\n• Afternoon (2:00 PM): Pine Forest walk. (Travel time: 10 mins from the market). Immerse yourself in the serene beauty of the pine forest. Capture the play of light and shadows through the trees.\n• Late Afternoon (4:00 PM): Visit the Betla National Park (Entry fee ₹100 per person, Gypsy Safari approx. ₹2500 for 2-3 hours). (Travel time: 2 hours, start early). While officially Betla is a separate destination requiring more time for complete exploration, you can get a glimpse of its outer areas from the Netarhat side. Consider a shorter safari ride if time permits. Focus on capturing the forest\'s beauty and wildlife from a distance.\n• Evening (7:00 PM): Dinner at a local restaurant. Try *Rugda* (a local mushroom dish) with rice. (₹400 for two)\n\n**Estimated Day 2 Cost (excluding hotel): ₹2030 per person (includes potential safari cost split between two)**\n\n**Day 3: Reflection and Departure**\n• Morning (8:00 AM): Visit the Mango Garden (Amra Vatika). A tranquil garden offering a peaceful escape. Capture the beauty of the mango trees and surrounding flora. (Entry Free)\n• Mid-morning (10:00 AM): Attend a local tribal dance or music performance (if available - inquire at your hotel for scheduled events). This is a unique opportunity to experience the rich cultural heritage of the region. (Cost varies – Estimate ₹500 donation/entry for two) Photography is often permitted, but always ask for permission first.\n• Afternoon (1:00 PM): Lunch at your hotel or a local restaurant. Relish a traditional Jharkhandi Thali (₹300 for two)\n• Afternoon (3:00 PM): Pack and prepare for departure.\n• Evening (4:00 PM): Depart from Netarhat.\n\n**Estimated Day 3 Cost (excluding hotel): ₹400 per person**\n\n**Important Notes Before You Start:**\n• **Respect:** Be mindful of local customs and traditions. Dress modestly, especially when visiting religious sites.\n• **Bargaining:** Bargain respectfully in local markets, but avoid excessive haggling.\n• **Environmental Responsibility:** Do not litter, dispose of waste responsibly, and avoid using plastic.\n• **Flexibility:** Be prepared for changes in weather conditions. Carry rain gear and appropriate clothing. Timings are estimates and can vary.\n• **Safety:** Netarhat is generally safe, but it\'s advisable to be cautious and avoid walking alone in isolated areas at night.\n• **Language:** Learn a few basic Hindi phrases such as \"Namaste\" (hello), \"Dhanyavaad\" (thank you), and \"Kitna hai?\" (How much?).\n\n**Accommodation Recommendation:**\n*Hotel Prabhat Vihar Netarhat*. Contact: +91 9431171433, +91 8292404187. This is a Jharkhand Tourism Development Corporation (JTDC) hotel, offering comfortable accommodation and a restaurant. It\'s centrally located and provides easy access to various attractions. Expect to pay around ₹3000 - ₹4000 per night for a double room.\n\n**Cultural Etiquette Tips for Tribal Areas:**\n• **Photography permissions:** Always ask for permission before taking photos of individuals, especially in tribal areas.\n• **Dress code recommendations:** Dress modestly, covering shoulders and knees, to respect local customs.\n• **Interaction guidelines:** Be polite and respectful when interacting with locals. Avoid making assumptions or generalizations about their culture.\n\n**Sustainable Tourism Practices:**\n• **Local economy support:** Purchase souvenirs and products from local artisans and vendors.\n• **Environmental conservation:** Support eco-friendly initiatives and avoid activities that harm the environment.\n• **Community respect:** Engage with the community in a respectful and responsible manner.\n\n**Practical Tips:**\n• **Best Time to Visit:** October to March (Winter season) for pleasant weather.\n• **Mobile Connectivity:** Limited network coverage. BSNL and Jio networks may work intermittently.\n• **Currency:** ATMs are available in Netarhat, but it\'s advisable to carry sufficient cash.\n• **Medical Facilities:** A basic clinic is available in Netarhat. For more serious medical issues, Ranchi is the nearest city with hospitals.\n\n**Important Contact Information:**\n• Railway Enquiry: 139\n• Tourist Information (Jharkhand Tourism): +91 651-2491552\n• Emergency Services: 112\n\n**Total Estimated Cost: ₹12,760 per person (including 2 nights hotel @ ₹3500/night), therefore ₹25,520 for 2 people**\n','{\"days\": 3, \"budget\": 25000, \"interests\": [\"Photography\"], \"group_size\": 2, \"destinations\": [\"Netarhat\"], \"travel_style\": \"balanced\"}','2025-09-19 00:24:16',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,'2025-09-19 05:54:15','2025-09-19 05:54:15'),('itinerary_20250919_071242','provider1','Betla National Park, Parasnath Hill',7,75000.00,'**TRIP PARAMETERS:**\n- Destinations: Betla National Park, Parasnath Hill\n- Duration: 7 days\n- Budget: ₹75000 for 3 people\n- Interests: Nightlife, Photography\n- Travel Style: balanced\n- Group Size: 3 people\n\n**Day 1: Arrival in Daltonganj & Betla Exploration**\n• Morning (8:00 AM): Arrival at Daltonganj Railway Station (DTO) from your origin city. Pre-booked taxi to Betla National Park (approx. 1.5 hours, ₹1500 for the taxi).\n• Mid-morning (10:00 AM): Check into your pre-booked accommodation near Betla. Freshen up.\n• Mid-morning (11:00 AM): Obtain permits for Betla National Park safari at the Forest Department Office (₹200 per person for entry, ₹800 for Gypsy hire). Consider hiring a local guide (₹500) for enhanced wildlife spotting and insights.\n• Afternoon (2:00 PM): Betla National Park Gypsy Safari (approx. 3 hours). Focus on photography opportunities around the Kechki Sangam and the Kamaldah Lake. Pack water and snacks.\n• Evening (6:00 PM): Relax at your accommodation.\n• Evening (8:00 PM): Dinner at a local dhaba near Betla, trying *Dhuska* (rice flour snack) and *Litti Chokha* (baked wheat balls with potato and eggplant mash) (₹300 per person). Minimal nightlife options in Betla. Stargazing opportunities if the sky is clear.\n\n**Estimated Day 1 Cost (excluding hotel): ₹1800 per person**\n\n**Day 2: Betla Fort & Tribal Culture**\n• Morning (8:00 AM): Visit Betla Fort (Old Fort & New Fort), exploring the historical ruins (₹50 per person). Capture the architectural details and scenic views.\n• Mid-morning (10:30 AM): Interact with the local Oraon tribe community. Visit a nearby village (ask your guide for assistance) to learn about their traditions, dance, and music. Respect their privacy and offer a small donation (₹200 per person).\n• Afternoon (1:00 PM): Lunch at your accommodation or a local restaurant. Try *Rugda* (a type of mushroom curry, seasonal). (₹350 per person).\n• Afternoon (3:00 PM): Visit the Palamu Tiger Reserve Interpretation Centre to learn more about the local flora and fauna. (₹100 per person).\n• Evening (6:00 PM): Participate in a traditional Oraon dance performance (if arranged through your guide, could cost ₹1000 for the group).\n• Evening (8:00 PM): Dinner at your accommodation.\n\n**Estimated Day 2 Cost (excluding hotel): ₹950 per person**\n\n**Day 3: Journey to Parasnath & Madhuban Exploration**\n• Morning (8:00 AM): Check out from your Betla accommodation.\n• Morning (8:30 AM): Hire a car to Parasnath (approx. 6-7 hours journey, ₹6000 for the entire car).\n• Afternoon (3:00 PM): Check into your pre-booked accommodation in Madhuban, the base of Parasnath Hill.\n• Afternoon (4:00 PM): Explore Madhuban. Visit the Bhomiyaji Asthan temple.\n• Evening (6:00 PM): Enjoy the sunset view from the base of Parasnath Hill. Photography opportunities abound.\n• Evening (8:00 PM): Dinner at a local vegetarian restaurant in Madhuban. Jain cuisine is prevalent. Try *Dal Baati Churma* (₹400 per person). Nightlife is limited due to the sacred nature of the location.\n\n**Estimated Day 3 Cost (excluding hotel): ₹2400 per person**\n\n**Day 4: Parasnath Hill Trek & Jain Temples**\n• Morning (4:00 AM): Begin the trek to Parasnath Hill summit. Carry water, snacks, and comfortable shoes. The trek is approximately 9 km uphill.\n• Morning (7:00 AM - 12:00 PM): Visit the various Jain temples (Tonks) dedicated to the 24 Tirthankaras situated atop the hill. Take photographs, but be mindful of the religious significance.\n• Afternoon (1:00 PM): Have packed lunch at a designated rest area on the hill (carry your own).\n• Afternoon (2:00 PM): Begin your descent.\n• Evening (5:00 PM): Relax at your accommodation.\n• Evening (8:00 PM): Dinner at your hotel or a local restaurant.\n\n**Estimated Day 4 Cost (excluding hotel): ₹500 per person (mostly for snacks and water)**\n\n**Day 5: Parasnath Temple Visit & Local Crafts**\n• Morning (9:00 AM): Visit the Shri Sammed Shikharji Jain Temple in Madhuban. Observe the rituals and learn about Jain philosophy.\n• Mid-morning (11:00 AM): Explore the local markets in Madhuban. Buy souvenirs, including local handicrafts and Jain religious items. Practice your bargaining skills (start at 50% of the quoted price).\n• Afternoon (1:00 PM): Lunch at a local restaurant. Try *Thekua* (a sweet snack popular in the region). (₹300 per person).\n• Afternoon (3:00 PM): Visit a local craft center (ask your hotel for recommendations) to witness the making of Jain religious art and textiles.\n• Evening (6:00 PM): Attend an Aarti (prayer ceremony) at the Shri Sammed Shikharji Jain Temple. (optional).\n• Evening (8:00 PM): Dinner at your hotel.\n\n**Estimated Day 5 Cost (excluding hotel): ₹700 per person (including potential souvenir purchases)**\n\n**Day 6: Return to Daltonganj & Relaxation**\n• Morning (9:00 AM): Check out from your Parasnath accommodation.\n• Morning (9:30 AM): Hire a car back to Daltonganj (approx. 6-7 hours journey, ₹6000 for the entire car).\n• Afternoon (4:00 PM): Check into a comfortable hotel in Daltonganj.\n• Evening (6:00 PM): Relax at the hotel. Perhaps enjoy a massage or spa treatment.\n• Evening (8:00 PM): Dinner at a restaurant in Daltonganj. Enjoy a wider variety of cuisines compared to Betla and Parasnath. (₹500 per person). You might find some options with music but don\'t expect a vibrant nightlife scene.\n\n**Estimated Day 6 Cost (excluding hotel): ₹2500 per person (including car, dinner, and potentially a massage)**\n\n**Day 7: Departure from Daltonganj**\n• Morning (9:00 AM): Visit the Koel View Point near Daltonganj for a panoramic view of the surrounding landscape. Capture some final photographs. (₹50 per person).\n• Mid-morning (11:00 AM): Visit the Daltonganj Market for some last-minute souvenir shopping.\n• Afternoon (1:00 PM): Lunch at a local restaurant. (₹300 per person).\n• Afternoon (3:00 PM): Transfer to Daltonganj Railway Station (DTO) for your departure.\n• Evening: Departure from Daltonganj.\n\n**Estimated Day 7 Cost (excluding hotel): ₹400 per person**\n\n**Important Notes Before You Start:**\n• **Respect:** Dress modestly, especially when visiting religious sites. Ask for permission before photographing people. Be mindful of local customs and traditions.\n• **Bargaining:** Bargain respectfully in local markets. A starting point of 50% of the quoted price is reasonable.\n• **Environmental Responsibility:** Avoid littering. Use reusable water bottles. Support eco-friendly tourism initiatives.\n• **Flexibility:** Weather conditions can affect travel plans. Be prepared to adjust your itinerary accordingly. Trekking might be difficult in heavy rain.\n• **Safety:** Be aware of your surroundings. Avoid walking alone at night in unfamiliar areas. Inform someone of your trekking plans. Keep emergency contact information handy.\n• **Language:** Basic Hindi phrases like \"Namaste\" (greetings), \"Dhanyavaad\" (thank you), \"Kitna hai?\" (how much?) will be helpful.\n\n**Accommodation Recommendation:**\n* **Betla:** Van Vihar is located inside Betla National Park. Contact: +91 94311 26597, email: forestdaltonganj@gmail.com. (Government-run, basic but convenient for safaris)\n* **Parasnath:** Hotel Parasnath, Madhuban. Contact: +91 99341 24003 (Decent amenities and near the base of the hill)\n* **Daltonganj:** Hotel Grand Shivam International, Daltonganj. Contact: +91 70910 00100 (More comfortable option in Daltonganj)\n\n**Cultural Etiquette Tips for Tribal Areas:**\n• Photography Permissions: Always ask for permission before taking photographs of individuals or tribal communities.\n• Dress Code Recommendations: Dress modestly. Avoid revealing clothing.\n• Interaction Guidelines: Be respectful and polite. Avoid making assumptions about their culture. Show genuine interest in learning about their traditions.\n\n**Sustainable Tourism Practices:**\n• Local Economy Support: Purchase souvenirs from local artisans and businesses. Eat at local restaurants. Hire local guides.\n• Environmental Conservation: Avoid single-use plastics. Dispose of waste responsibly. Support conservation efforts in the area.\n• Community Respect: Be mindful of local customs and traditions. Avoid disrupting the peace and tranquility of the area.\n\n**Practical Tips:**\n• **Best Time to Visit:** October to March is the ideal time to visit Betla National Park and Parasnath Hill, due to pleasant weather.\n• **Mobile Connectivity:** Mobile network coverage is generally good in Daltonganj and Madhuban. Coverage may be spotty inside Betla National Park and on Parasnath Hill.\n• **Currency:** ATMs are available in Daltonganj and near Parasnath. It\'s advisable to carry sufficient cash, especially for transactions in smaller villages and shops.\n• **Medical Facilities:**\n    * **Daltonganj:** Sadar Hospital (Government Hospital) - Contact Number: +91 6562 222041\n    * **Madhuban:** Basic medical facilities are available. For serious medical needs, Daltonganj is the nearest option.\n\n**Important Contact Information:**\n• Railway Enquiry: 139\n• Tourist Information (Jharkhand Tourism): +91 651 249 2322\n• Emergency Services: 112\n\n**Total Estimated Cost: ₹ 65,850 for 3 people (excluding accommodation)** This leaves approximately ₹9150 for accommodation for the 3 people, allowing an average of ₹1300 per night for rooms, which is reasonable for the suggested locations.\n\n**Note:** All costs are estimates and can vary depending on your choices and travel style. Pre-booking accommodation and transportation, especially during peak season, is highly recommended. The specific numbers given for activities are estimates, but are realistic.\n','{\"days\": 7, \"budget\": 75000, \"interests\": [\"Nightlife\", \"Photography\"], \"group_size\": 3, \"destinations\": [\"Betla National Park\", \"Parasnath Hill\"], \"travel_style\": \"balanced\"}','2025-09-19 01:42:43',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,'2025-09-19 07:12:42','2025-09-19 07:12:42');
